args: Boy, I am BORED. And now that I've\nfinished reading every book in the library,\nthere's REALLY nothing left to do!
...Hmm? That's Elisanne and Cleo\nin the kitchen?
Then why do you seem so flustered?
We are about to do some baking.
We are baking a chocolate cake.
In that case, I want in on this action.\nI was bored stiff!
We'll be happy to have you—not that we\nseem to have any say in the matter.
I have never baked a cake before.\nHave you done so, Ezelith?
Nope! I'm a total kitchen noob.
Then we are on the same level.\nLet us both give it our utmost!
Have you finished melting the chocolate\nand the butter? If so, you must move on\nto the meringue.
I must whip these egg whites, yes?\nSuch manual labor should come as\nsecond nature to me, I imagine.
I'm gonna whip mine up real good\nand get plenty of air in there!
Next, you both need to fold\nthe meringue into the batter.
Make sure to do so gently, so the\nmeringue doesn't lose its air.
Gently... Gently... Like...this?\nAh! I think I have it!
Done! Oh man, this puppy is PERFECT.
Look how fluffy the sponge is!\nMan, I scare myself sometimes.
You're right. I can't find a single fault in it.
AND it tastes amazing!\nI really am a genius...
Stellar work, Ezelith. It's hard to\nimagine we both have the same\namount of experience.
That's right, keep the praise coming!
I fear my cake has the same shape and\nconsistency of a Halidom brick.
Wow, you're right. It hasn't risen at ALL.
You likely used a bit too much strength\nwhen folding the meringue and batter.
My apologies. I tried to work as carefully\nas possible, but perhaps that proved my\nundoing in the end.
Baking is all about learning from failure.\nAllow yourself a moment to relax,\nthen start again from the beginning.
Yeah, so what if you made a mistake?\nJust keep at it until you don't!
I mean, everyone's got stuff they aren't\ngood at. ...Well, except me, but I'm\nan incredibly rare exception.
Oh, I was just thinking that it's unusual\nfor you to be encouraging someone.
I guess I just felt like it, is all.\nYou got a problem with that?
What got you two so fired up\nabout making cakes, anyway?
If we tell you, you are forbidden from\nspeaking a word of it to anyone.
We are trying to fashion a small token\nof our thanks and admiration.
The heck are you talking about?
Valentine's is a time where you give\nboth presents and thanks to people.
The sweets, chocolate, and other items\nyou give around then are very special!
If you say so. Well, let's get back to work.\nWhat are you going to do, Ezelith?
Do you have any interest in\ncontinuing to bake with us?
Those two looked like they were having\nso much fun making their cakes...
Is ＂thanks＂ really such a special thing?\nCan it REALLY make people that happy?
I don't think I get it.
I don't think I get it at ALL!
